<p>
We use the
<a href="geom-lp.html">ellipsoid method</a>
to develop (theoretically) efficient algorithms
for optimizing linear functions on intersections of
<a href="geom-zono.html">zonotopes</a>,
and show how to apply this to train soft-margin support vector classifiers.
<p>
(<a href="/~eppstein/bibs/eppstein.html#Optimization over zonotopes and training support vector machines">BibTeX</a> &ndash;
